{
  "stem": "2718.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "At the same time, everybody observed the Shabbat.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and it would have been-- I think it was, to my knowledge, nobody ever ate, even after the [INAUDIBLE], a trace of food.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "No need to say that we observed all the holidays.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in Hungary, there were two types of people-- actually three, but the third one was very much a minority.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "One was the so-called-- I'm talking about Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "One was so-called [NON-ENGLISH], which is-- it's not a Reform, because at that time, there was no-- no such a thing as Reform.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Not in Hungary anyway, there was in Germany.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They were-- they didn't observe the Shabbat, but at the same time they observed all the holidays.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "More or less they kept kosher, but-- but not so 100%.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And-- and they were, like everybody else, they were more Jews of convenience.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "What was convenient for them, that was the same as Jews they were.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Then-- then came our section which was more observant.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the children were brought up [? like ?] myself.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I had my education in the-- in the Jewish gymnasium, which is equal to Jewish high school like [?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Moriah ?] here.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] and naturally, we put far more importance on religion and being Jewish than the one-- I wouldn't say-- I wouldn't use the word below us, because other people would take offense-- but not next to us.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Then we had a very-- we had also people with-- very religious people, ultrareligious people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "There was [NON-ENGLISH] and beard and [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And there was a yeshiva in-- in Budapest, who were not-- not close to us, not because we didn't respect them by any means, but because they had a different lifestyle.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
